WHMurray@DOCKMASTER.NCSC.MIL wrote:

: If you feel that the value of your intellectual property relies upon
: world wide use, then trade secret is the only way to go.  No one
: understands that better than the inventors of RSA; their invention is
: exploited everywhere in the world except in the one country that granted
: them a patent.  The inventors of an invention more novel and less
: obvious than the microchip are systematically and intentionally denied
: the compensation that the founders intended.  Many who post to this list
: seem to begrudge them any compensation at all.

: Coca-Cola has always understood it.

Coca-cola is made under licence in dozens of countries around the
world.  You're crazy if you think PepsiCo doesn't know the recipe.
The same will be true if RC[n] becomes widely used.

Andrew.
